CVE Cross-Scope Bug Detection Pipeline

This project analyzes Linux CVE announcements to detect cross-scope bugs.

## Setup

1. Set environment variables:
   export OPENAI_API_KEY="your-api-key"
   export OPENAI_BASE_URL="https://your-endpoint/api/"  # optional

2. Install dependencies (if any)

3. Ensure ctags is installed: `sudo apt install universal-ctags` or equivalent

## Usage

Run the pipeline: `python pipeline.py`

The pipeline will:
- Fetch emails sequentially from linux-cve-announce/git/
- Use LLM to analyze for potential cross-domain bugs and extract call stacks/versions
- Checkout corresponding kernel versions
- Extract function definitions
- Judge for cross-scope errors
- Append titles of cross-scope bugs to results.txt

## Files

- fetch.py: Email fetching utilities
- llm_safe.py: LLM interaction
- pipeline.py: Main workflow
- source_manager.py: Kernel source management
- extractor.py: Function extraction
- cve.py: Version parsing utilities